consent:
Principal Investigators: Chandler Robinson, University of Utah



Key Information

Please take time to review this information carefully. This is a research study. Your participation in this study is voluntary, which means you may choose not to participate or to withdraw at any time without penalty or loss of benefits. You may ask the researchers any questions about the study before or during your participation. If you decide to take part, you will be asked to indicate your consent. Please ensure you understand what participation involves, including any potential risks or benefits.



What is the purpose of this study?

Thank you for your interest in our research study on how people perceive police officers based on visual characteristics. This study is conducted by researchers at the University of Utah. The purpose is to assess how people interpret and evaluate AI-generated images of police officers that vary by race, gender, and body type. The collected data will be used exclusively for scientific purposes and to inform future experimental research on public perceptions of law enforcement. We aim to enroll approximately 500 participants in this study.



What will I do if I choose to be in this study?

If you agree to participate, you will view a series of AI-generated police officer profile images and be asked to: Identify characteristics (e.g., race, gender, body type) of each officer image, evalutate officer impressions, or identify changes across officers. You will also answer a few demographic questions.



How long will I be in the study?

Participation will take approximately 4-6 minutes. Submissions that deviate substantially from this expected range may be flagged for quality review.



What are the possible risks or discomforts?

This study involves minimal risk. You will be shown static images and asked non-invasive questions. Some images or trait judgments may prompt personal reflection or discomfort, but you may stop at any time. No identifying or sensitive information will be collected. Please review and agree to Prolific’s participant, privacy, and compensation policies prior to participation. There are no direct costs to participate.



Are there any potential benefits? 

While there are no direct benefits, you may gain insight into how people evaluate visual information about law enforcement. The findings may help researchers better understand how visual cues shape public attitudes toward police, potentially informing future policy and accountability practices.



Will I receive payment or other incentive?

You will receive compensation in accordance with Prolific’s policies. The survey is priced to reflect a rate of $12/hour. Full payment will be issued upon valid completion of the survey.



Which personal data are collected and processed?

We will collect basic demographic information including age, gender, race/ethnicity, education, and political affiliation. We may also collect information about your social or political views relevant to policing or public safety.



Will information about me and my participation be kept confidential?

Yes. All responses will be collected anonymously through Qualtrics and stored securely on encrypted servers at the University of Utah. No identifying information (e.g., name, IP address) will be collected. Survey data will be kept confidential and used only for scientific analysis and publication in anonymized form.



What are my rights if I take part in this study?

Participation is entirely voluntary. You may choose not to participate or to withdraw at any time without penalty or loss of compensation (unless incomplete per Prolific’s policies).



Who can I contact if I have questions about the study? 

If you have questions about the research, your rights as a participant, or wish to withdraw, please contact: 



Chandler Robinson, University of Utah: chandler.robinson@utah.edu



If you have concerns you do not wish to discuss with the research team, or wish to report a complaint, you may contact the University of Utah Institutional Review Board (IRB):



IRB Contact: Phone: (801) 581-3655 | Email: irb@hsc.utah.edu



Consent Statement

I understand that my participation is voluntary and that I may withdraw from the study at any time without penalty. I confirm that: 



I am at least 18 years old.



I have read and understood the study information above.



I consent to the anonymous collection and use of my data for scientific research purposes.



I agree to the storage of anonymized data on secure servers during the study period.



I understand that anonymized findings may be published in academic outlets.



I voluntarily consent to participate in this research study.
